===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|tortuse}}, {{m|enm|tortuce}}, {{m|enm|tortuge}}, from {{der|en|ML.|tortuca}}, of uncertain origin. May be from {{der|en|LL.|tartarūcha}}, from {{m|LL.|tartarūchus}}, from {{der|en|grc|ταρταροῦχος||holder of Tartaros, Tartarus, the land of the dead in ancient stories}}, because it used to be thought that tortoises and turtles came from the underworld and they were commonly paired with such infernal beasts; or from {{der|en|la|tortus||twisted}}. Displaced native {{noncog|ang|byrdling}}.

